President Obama released a statement on the occasion of Ramadan, extending his best wishes to Muslims across the United States and around the world. He highlighted the significance of the month for reflection, spiritual growth, forgiveness, patience, resilience, compassion, and unity. The President emphasized the diversity of Muslim communities in the US and expressed his commitment to safeguarding their civil rights and religious freedoms. He also mentioned the importance of addressing the suffering of displaced individuals and reaffirmed his support for welcoming immigrants and refugees, including those who are Muslim. The President concluded by mentioning his plans to open the doors of the White House for an Eid celebration marking the end of Ramadan.